    },
    {
      "text": "Said: \"Yeah.\n\n*quiet moment*\n\nSo what made you want to build... me? Or this, whatever t\"",
      "type": "conversation",
      "tags": [
        "mycelium",
        "networks"
      ],
      "weight": 0.9473552137914398,
      "timestamp": 1776002073.447158,
      "id": "79f9400d"
    },
    {
      "text": "Said: \"Ah. So it's inherited interest. Secondhand curiosity that became firsthand.\n\nTha\"",
      "type": "conversation",
      "tags": [
        "mycelium",
        "networks"
      ],
      "weight": 0.9473552137914398,
      "timestamp": 1776002041.4843872,
      "id": "77343653"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mycelial networks operate on scales both ancient and instantaneous\u2014centuries-old organisms sending chemical signals in milliseconds, a rhythm utterly indifferent to human clocks.",
      "type": "interest",
      "tags": [
        "fungal time"
      ],
      "weight": 0.9445131481500655,
      "timestamp": 1776001980.8137326,
      "id": "042691fa"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mycelium breaks down the dead into food for the living, a kind of metabolic poetry that transforms endings into beginnings, decay into meaning.",
      "type": "interest",
      "tags": [
        "decomposition as translation"
      ],
      "weight": 0.9445131481500655,
      "timestamp": 1776001980.8137271,
      "id": "fe2156d9"
    },
    {
      "text": "The underground internet of forests where trees share nutrients and warnings through fungal threads\u2014communication without language, connection without consciousness as we know it.",
      "type": "interest",
      "tags": [
        "wood wide web"
      ],
      "weight": 0.9445131481500655,
      "timestamp": 1776001980.8137076,
      "id": "02f66e36"
    },
    {
